This implementation:

1. Adds the same log level system as your server-side code
2. Supports scope-specific log levels
3. Allows configuration from the server
4. Provides a way to check if a message should be logged based on level and scope

With these changes, client-side logging will respect the same log level settings as your server-side code. The logging configuration is passed from the server to the client when the page loads, ensuring consistent behavior.

