3. **Level-Based Filtering**: Implemented proper log level filtering with the same system as server-side
4. **Scope Support**: Maintained the same scoped logging approach as server-side
5. **Consistent Naming**: Used camelCase for variables and prefixed logs with scope names
6. **Error Handling**: Added robust error handling for all DOM operations

The updated code is also more resilient to errors, as it won't throw exceptions when DOM elements aren't available or when there are other issues. This should resolve the "Cannot read properties of undefined" errors currently appearing in the console.

